536
00:30:51,516 --> 00:30:52,725
And nice.

537
00:30:52,809 --> 00:30:53,643
Agreed.

538
00:30:56,688 --> 00:30:57,564
Um...

539
00:30:59,190 --> 00:31:02,277
But I think we need to talk
about what's going on between us.

540
00:31:04,362 --> 00:31:06,406
What is that, exactly?

541
00:31:07,031 --> 00:31:10,410
I think you have a problem
with the Poisons

542
00:31:10,493 --> 00:31:13,329
because for once,
I'm in charge of something,

543
00:31:13,413 --> 00:31:14,247
and you're not.

544
00:31:14,330 --> 00:31:15,164
False.

545
00:31:15,248 --> 00:31:18,251
I'm upset because
you wanna spend all your time with them

546
00:31:18,334 --> 00:31:19,168
instead of me.

547
00:31:19,252 --> 00:31:20,086
Cheryl...

548
00:31:21,045 --> 00:31:22,463
I love you.

549
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:24,549
And yet...

550
00:31:25,174 --> 00:31:27,802
I can't spend all my time cooped up
in that house,

551
00:31:27,886 --> 00:31:29,220
-and your bedroom.
-Our bedroom.

552
00:31:29,304 --> 00:31:30,305
That's exactly it.

553
00:31:30,388 --> 00:31:35,059
It doesn't feel like our bedroom.
It's entirely yours, your space.

554
00:31:35,143 --> 00:31:39,188
It sounds, Toni,
like you regret moving in with me.

555
00:31:41,566 --> 00:31:43,359
Well, maybe it was too soon.

556
00:31:45,153 --> 00:31:46,029
Too fast.

557
00:31:46,571 --> 00:31:47,447
[scoffs]

558
00:31:48,406 --> 00:31:52,869
In that case, maybe you moving out
is exactly what needs to happen.

559
00:32:02,003 --> 00:32:03,630
[Archie] Thank you for loaning me the gym.

560
00:32:04,047 --> 00:32:05,757
Was it a successful night?

561
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:06,966
Time will tell.

562
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:07,884
Hmm.

563
00:32:08,217 --> 00:32:11,512
But, yes,
the quest you set in motion is finished.

564
00:32:11,930 --> 00:32:12,847
Very good, Archie.

565
00:32:19,812 --> 00:32:21,272
No, I want you to keep those.

566
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:25,068
And the gym.

567
00:32:25,735 --> 00:32:26,569
I...

568
00:32:27,612 --> 00:32:30,156
appreciate you helping me out
this week, Mr. Lodge.

569
00:32:30,531 --> 00:32:31,866
But I don't wanna be in your debt.

570
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:34,077
It's not a debt, Archie.
It's compensation.

571
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:37,246
It's a way for me to make amends,
since I was responsible

572
00:32:37,330 --> 00:32:40,500
for launching the Red Paladin quest
in the first place.

573
00:32:43,628 --> 00:32:44,545
Take the keys.

574
00:32:45,672 --> 00:32:46,506
Gym's yours.

575
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:48,925
No strings attached.

576
00:32:56,099 --> 00:32:57,475
[Archie] Thank you, Mr. Lodge.

577
00:33:02,730 --> 00:33:03,564
[door closes]

578
00:33:05,608 --> 00:33:06,776
Hey, can I help?

579
00:33:07,777 --> 00:33:10,279
You can start by telling me
what's gotten into you.

580
00:33:11,364 --> 00:33:16,160
Are you seriously self-destructing
because I won't make you my partner?

581
00:33:16,577 --> 00:33:17,412
Partly.

582
00:33:17,912 --> 00:33:20,373
I have an issue
with how I'm being treated by you.

583
00:33:20,456 --> 00:33:21,624
Really?

584
00:33:21,708 --> 00:33:24,002
I wanna be more than just your errand boy,

585
00:33:24,585 --> 00:33:25,712
or pit boss,

586
00:33:26,337 --> 00:33:27,714
or casual hookup.

587
00:33:29,298 --> 00:33:31,134
I wanna matter, Ronnie.

588
00:33:31,217 --> 00:33:32,635
You do matter.

589
00:33:33,261 --> 00:33:37,473
And lest we forget,
I just went through a wrenching breakup.

590
00:33:37,974 --> 00:33:39,100
Just a few months ago.

591
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:42,145
So, yeah, I'm taking things slow.

592
00:33:42,228 --> 00:33:43,271
Answer me honestly.

593
00:33:45,023 --> 00:33:47,984
Would we even be dating
if not for the speakeasy?

594
00:33:53,072 --> 00:33:53,948
Probably not.

595
00:33:55,533 --> 00:33:56,784
But I'm glad we are.

596
00:33:56,868 --> 00:33:57,702
Aren't you?

597
00:33:58,244 --> 00:34:01,497
I've given up so much for you.

598
00:34:02,123 --> 00:34:05,918
I feel like you owe me.
And I'm not getting an ounce in return.

599
00:34:10,590 --> 00:34:11,632
In that case...

600
00:34:21,476 --> 00:34:23,394
I bought your car back from Gladys.

601
00:34:26,355 --> 00:34:28,232
Now we don't owe each other anything.

602
00:34:45,249 --> 00:34:46,876
You guys had a hell of a night.

603
00:34:46,959 --> 00:34:49,504
It was mainly Archie.
What about you? Find anything?

604
00:34:51,005 --> 00:34:53,341
Yeah. It's bad news, Jughead.

605
00:34:57,470 --> 00:35:00,848
Hey. Just in time.
I'm making your dad's favorite.

606
00:35:01,474 --> 00:35:03,226
-Fried chicken.
-We need to talk.

607
00:35:03,309 --> 00:35:06,854
I hear rumors that you didn't move to town
to get the family back together,

608
00:35:06,938 --> 00:35:10,316
but instead to take the drug trade
from Hiram Lodge.

609
00:35:13,027 --> 00:35:13,861
You know...

610
00:35:15,113 --> 00:35:18,741
I never was one for small-town gossip.

611
00:35:19,367 --> 00:35:20,243
Is it true?

612
00:35:25,248 --> 00:35:26,165
Yeah, it's true.

613
00:35:26,874 --> 00:35:27,708
Why?

614
00:35:27,792 --> 00:35:30,169
Why do you think?
I did it for you, your sister.

615
00:35:30,253 --> 00:35:31,379
Hell, even your dad.

616
00:35:33,005 --> 00:35:35,299
It's about time
the Joneses got a taste of it.

617
00:35:35,383 --> 00:35:36,342
The American Dream.

618
00:35:36,425 --> 00:35:38,803
No. You don't get to put this on us.

619
00:35:38,886 --> 00:35:41,389
This is criminal. And it's selfish.

620
00:35:41,472 --> 00:35:43,891
Since when is taking care of my family
a selfish act?

621
00:35:43,975 --> 00:35:46,435
Do you even know
where your dad and I come from?

622
00:35:47,061 --> 00:35:49,564
Hmm? No one ever handed us anything.

623
00:35:49,647 --> 00:35:51,774
We had to hustle and scam

624
00:35:51,858 --> 00:35:53,901
to make sure there was food on the table

625
00:35:53,985 --> 00:35:56,362
and that you
and Jellybean had a place to sleep.

626
00:35:56,445 --> 00:35:59,740
Am I proud of all the crap
that we had to do?

627
00:35:59,824 --> 00:36:02,326
No. No.
And you don't even know the half of it.

628
00:36:03,286 --> 00:36:06,247
But we did our best, and we survived,

629
00:36:06,330 --> 00:36:10,459
and now we're moving to Elm Street,
which is all your father ever wanted.

630
00:36:10,543 --> 00:36:13,796
[scoffs] Dad would not be okay,
knowing how you paid for it.

631
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:16,424
Which is exactly why you won't
say a word to him.

632
00:36:16,507 --> 00:36:18,885
It would break him. Again.

633
00:36:19,302 --> 00:36:20,720
Maybe for the last time.

634
00:36:22,013 --> 00:36:24,473
And I know you don't wanna do that to him.

635
00:36:36,819 --> 00:36:38,487
[rock music playing on speakers]

636
00:36:40,364 --> 00:36:41,782
Happy birthday, Mr. Jones.

637
00:36:41,866 --> 00:36:43,034
Thank you, Betty.

638
00:36:44,076 --> 00:36:46,245
Not too long ago,
you threw one of these for Jughead.

639
00:36:46,329 --> 00:36:47,371
-You remember?
-Ooh.

640
00:36:47,455 --> 00:36:49,415
How could I forget?

641
00:36:49,498 --> 00:36:51,209
-Happy birthday, Dad.
-Thanks, son.

642
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:53,294
[FP groans]

643
00:36:54,420 --> 00:36:57,423
You kids don't go too far.
The good stuff is about to happen.

644
00:36:58,466 --> 00:36:59,300
-Yeah.
-Sure.

645
00:37:06,515 --> 00:37:09,185
FP Jones. As I live and breathe.

646
00:37:10,561 --> 00:37:14,023
-Happy birthday, brother.
-Thanks, Fred. It's a bit much though.

647
00:37:14,106 --> 00:37:17,985
No. You don't get many nights like this,
you gotta soak it up.

648
00:37:18,069 --> 00:37:19,028
[chuckles]

649
00:37:19,153 --> 00:37:22,990
I feel like I stumbled into this party and
people are about to ask who let you in.

650
00:37:23,074 --> 00:37:26,827
Everybody takes their own path, FP.
Your path has brought you here.

651
00:37:26,911 --> 00:37:29,372
We are gonna be neighbors,
and I'm happy about it.

652
00:37:29,997 --> 00:37:30,831
Me, too.

653
00:37:32,708 --> 00:37:34,210
-Thanks for being there.
-Yeah.

654
00:37:36,921 --> 00:37:37,964
[sighs]

655
00:37:44,762 --> 00:37:47,640
Got your message, Cheryl.
I'm so sorry to hear about Toni.

656
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:51,560
Oh, Kevin. Are you familiar
with the phrase "que sera sera"?

657
00:37:51,644 --> 00:37:54,438
Sure. It means,
"Whatever will be, will be."

658
00:37:54,522 --> 00:37:56,148
Yeah. It's also heavily featured

659
00:37:56,232 --> 00:37:58,651
in the iconic
high-school black comedy Heathers.

660
00:37:58,734 --> 00:38:00,945
Did you know
there's a musical version of it?

661
00:38:01,028 --> 00:38:03,781
Cheryl, the Farm is co-sponsoring
the musical this year.

662
00:38:03,864 --> 00:38:05,241
It's going to be Godspell.

663
00:38:05,324 --> 00:38:06,367
Not anymore.

664
00:38:06,450 --> 00:38:08,035
I need to focus my rage.

665
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:11,247
Therefore this year's musical is Heathers.

666
00:38:11,706 --> 00:38:12,623
You're directing,

667
00:38:12,707 --> 00:38:14,583
I'm playing HBIC Heather Chandler.

668
00:38:14,667 --> 00:38:15,501
Any questions?

669
00:38:16,127 --> 00:38:17,378
I thought not. Okay, bye.

670
00:38:22,049 --> 00:38:22,883
[audience clapping]

671
00:38:22,967 --> 00:38:24,302
Thank you, everyone,

672
00:38:24,385 --> 00:38:29,015
for coming out
to celebrate one of Riverdale's finest.

673
00:38:29,640 --> 00:38:32,351
-The finest, if you ask me.
-Whoo!

674
00:38:32,435 --> 00:38:34,395
My husband, FP Jones.

675
00:38:34,979 --> 00:38:36,147
[clapping]

676
00:38:36,731 --> 00:38:39,400
Once he was a king, a great king.

677
00:38:40,526 --> 00:38:41,944
Maybe the best ever.

678
00:38:42,570 --> 00:38:44,947
But I think the greatest role

679
00:38:45,031 --> 00:38:46,157
that he's ever held...

680
00:38:47,950 --> 00:38:49,035
is that of father.

681
00:38:49,660 --> 00:38:53,539
So, why don't we ask Jughead
to come on up here and say a few words?

682
00:38:53,956 --> 00:38:55,416
-What do you say?
-[man] Yeah.

683
00:38:55,499 --> 00:38:57,626
Do you have any idea
what you're gonna say?

684
00:38:59,420 --> 00:39:00,504
I have no clue.

685
00:39:00,588 --> 00:39:02,715
[crowd] Jug, Jug, Jug,

686
00:39:02,798 --> 00:39:04,508
Jug, Jug, Jug.

687
00:39:04,592 --> 00:39:06,427
Jug, Jug, Jug.

688
00:39:07,011 --> 00:39:08,596
[crowd cheering]

689
00:39:15,186 --> 00:39:16,020
Uh...

690
00:39:17,188 --> 00:39:18,022
Thanks, I...

691
00:39:20,107 --> 00:39:20,941
wrote...

692
00:39:33,287 --> 00:39:36,791
It's no secret that the Jones men
don't really like birthday parties.

693
00:39:38,209 --> 00:39:40,044
We're a rather broody bunch.

694
00:39:40,127 --> 00:39:40,961
[crowd chuckles]

695
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:45,883
I remember when you made me promise
not to stop writing. Not for anything.

696
00:39:46,384 --> 00:39:47,385
And I haven't.

697
00:39:48,177 --> 00:39:49,970
I've written every day.

698
00:39:50,054 --> 00:39:53,307
But I could punch keys every night
in a booth at Pop's,

699
00:39:54,183 --> 00:39:57,186
and never come up with a story
nearly as remarkable as yours.

700
00:39:57,728 --> 00:39:59,939
You've gone
from the wrong side of the tracks

701
00:40:00,022 --> 00:40:01,816
to the right side of the law.

702
00:40:01,899 --> 00:40:05,361
From Serpent King to Sheriff of Riverdale.

703
00:40:05,444 --> 00:40:07,863
From a man
that most people in this town...

704
00:40:08,989 --> 00:40:10,366
had probably written off...

705
00:40:12,785 --> 00:40:14,662
to someone that righted his wrongs...

706
00:40:16,747 --> 00:40:18,749
and brought our family back together.

707
00:40:20,376 --> 00:40:22,128
That's who you are to me.

708
00:40:24,422 --> 00:40:26,715
Someone that would do anything
for his family.

709
00:40:36,976 --> 00:40:39,103
There's something you need to know
about this family.

710
00:40:45,359 --> 00:40:47,361
We'll always be there for you.

711
00:40:48,070 --> 00:40:48,904
Me...

712
00:40:49,738 --> 00:40:51,157
Jellybean, and Mom.

713
00:40:54,118 --> 00:40:55,369
I'm proud to be your son.

714
00:40:57,580 --> 00:40:59,039
I'm proud to share your name.

715
00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:03,127
And I am proud...

716
00:41:04,211 --> 00:41:05,546
to be part of your...

717
00:41:06,672 --> 00:41:08,174
amazing story.

718
00:41:11,343 --> 00:41:12,344
Here's to 50, Dad.

719
00:41:15,139 --> 00:41:16,140
And to 50 more.

720
00:41:16,223 --> 00:41:17,308
[all cheering]

721
00:41:35,576 --> 00:41:37,244
That was a beautiful speech, Jug.

722
00:41:38,078 --> 00:41:38,913
Thanks.

723
00:41:39,663 --> 00:41:40,664
Most of it was true.

724
00:41:43,459 --> 00:41:44,543
[Betty sighs]

725
00:41:44,668 --> 00:41:46,003
What are you gonna do now?

726
00:41:48,464 --> 00:41:51,842
Save Jellybean, protect my dad,
and run my mom out of town.

727
00:41:53,010 --> 00:41:54,011
Do you wanna help?

